raw_data.title: Entrust Managed Services (Fed SSP) PIV Certs
raw_data.description: The Entrust Federal Shared Service Provider (Fed SSP) is a hosted PKI offering for employees of the US Federal Government, or their contractors where a US Federal department has sponsored their contractor.   The hosted Federal SSP CA is subordinate to the Entrust Federal Root CA, which in turn is cross-certified with the Federal Common Policy CA. Certificates it is able to offer are: PIV and User, Device, Server. Up to 101 - 500  (per entity)
